modules.description: Provides block device operations such as reading and writing sectors, initializing storage, and managing device geometry. Works with raw byte arrays and sector-based data structures for low-level storage access. Used to interface with disk images in unikernel environments running on Solo5.

Provides pretty-printers for error and write error types, and functions to connect, disconnect, and query block devices. Supports reading from and writing to block devices using lists of buffer chunks aligned to sector boundaries. Enables interaction with block storage systems, including handling I/O operations and device-specific information retrieval.
